TY  - JOUR
AU  - Saffi, Pedro A. C.
AU  - Sigurdsson, Kari
T1  - Price Efficiency and Short Selling
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhq124
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 24
IS  - 3
SP  - 821
EP  - 852
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This article presents a study of how stock price efficiency and return distributions are affected by short-sale constraints. The study is based on a global dataset, from 2005 to 2008, that includes more than 12,600 stocks from 26 countries. We present two main findings. First, lending supply has a significant impact on efficiency. Stocks with higher short-sale constraints, measured as low lending supply, have lower price efficiency. Second, relaxing short-sales constraints is not associated with an increase in either price instability or the occurrence of extreme negative returns.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhq124
ER  - 



