T1  - Do Peso Problems Explain the Returns to the Carry Trade?
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhq138
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 24
IS  - 3
SP  - 853
EP  - 891
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study the properties of the carry trade, a currency speculation strategy in which an investor borrows low-interest-rate currencies and lends high-interest-rate currencies. This strategy generates payoffs that are on average large and uncorrelated with traditional risk factors. We argue that these payoffs reflect a peso problem. The underlying peso event features high values of the stochastic discount factor rather than very large negative payoffs.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhq138
ER  - 



